Summaries for SLC4A2 Gene

GeneCards Summary for SLC4A2 Gene

SLC4A2 (Solute Carrier Family 4 Member 2) is a Protein Coding gene. Diseases associated with SLC4A2 include primary biliary cirrhosis. Among its related pathways are Bile secretion and Salivary secretion. GO annotations related to this gene include transporter activity and anion transmembrane transporter activity. An important paralog of this gene is SLC4A8.

UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot for SLC4A2 Gene

  • B3A2_HUMAN,P04920

  • Plasma membrane anion exchange protein of wide distribution.
